<paragraph id="82053714CBA972A65096C1EEB82439C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="796825ED9B3140BFCEFE3552531FE026" pageId="0" pageNumber="127">This new species can be distinguished from its regional congeners by the following combination of characters: in profile, posterior margin of head anteroposteriorly compressed; limited number of hair pairs on body: two pairs on posterior margin of head, two to three pairs on promesonotum, and one to two pairs on first gastral tergite.</paragraph>
